OL,6,FOn Friday, Health Minister Robin Swann
OL,7,Fannounced the reinstatement of #85,000
OL,8,Fof funding to the hospice.JHe also
OL,9,Facknowledged the move will not be
OL,10,Fenough to prevent the announced
OL,11,Freduction in some services at the
OL,12,Ffacility.JMr Swann asked officials to
OL,13,Flook "urgently" at the planned bed
OL,14,Fcuts to determine the best way
OL,15,Fforward.JHe also announced changes to
OL,16,Fhow the core funding is structured
OL,17,Fgoing forward.JThe minister said the
OL,18,F#1.6million currently includes
OL,19,F#420,000 that is non-recurring money
OL,20,Fand which requires annual approval.JMr
OL,21,FSwann said that the #420,000 would be
OL,22,Frecurring from now on ` a move he said
OL,23,Fwould provide "greater certainty" for
OL,24,Fthe hospice.JOn Monday, the hospice
OL,25,Fsaid it was "grateful for and
OL,26,Freassured by" its core funding
